values: Instead of doing anything productive with my life I have been watching Captain Planet on youtube. For a good laugh search captain planet Hitler.

For those of you that don't know I accepted an offer to go to Penn State College of Medicine for a PhD next fall. I am happy with my decsision and have been searching for apartments and getting excited about living in Hershey for the next 5 years. However I recieved this email today...

Dear Daniel,
I am serving as the chair of the graduate admissions committee in the
Department of Molecular Bioloy at Princeton University.
As you know, you were put on the waitlist. We now have our final tally of
accepts versus declines for the fall, and we are able to go to the waitlist
and admit one or two more students. You are high up on our waitlist and I am
therefore emailing to see whether you are still interested.
If so, I could ask the graduate school to admit you, and if they agree, we
will help you to de-enrol from whatever other University you may by now have
sent your acceptance letter to.
Please let me know asap whether you are still interested in our program at
Princeton, and don't hesitate asking any questions you may have.

Best regards
Trudi Schupbach

Is going to  a Coca-Cola school better than the generic brand school. It will probably be less stressful at Penn State and a PhD is a PhD no matter where you get it. How much do employers care about the school you went to anyway? How much will I like living in Jersey?  Do anyone have words of wisdom?

So I thought the time to register for Fall and Summer classes for seniors and grad students was last night. I tried to register for field camp last night and the system let me in but said I needed Dept. permission. I got an overide this afternoon and I registered with no problems. Now I find out that Seniors and grad students don't actually register till Wednesday. Hmmm, how was I able to do this so early? Do presidents scholars get to go before everyone else?

One week ago I stabbed myself with a syringe and bled a lot. Today I inhaled too much of the drug 5-FI which is a poison for Chamydomonas at 5 uM. I also stared directly into a UV light box on full power to get a better look at my sample and I only stopped because my eyes were starting to black out. To top it off I spilled a carcnogen on my shoe.

I just wanted to share that an extream rare occasion took place a minute ago. I found out that I do not have a final on the last day.  I am totally done with my undergraduate life at 3pm May 1st.  I will not be done with Lehigh since I'm going to field camp in June but thats different.

Wow I just found out the most amazing thing. I was doing some research on the University of Pittsburgh for my interview and I wanted to find out more about potential teaching responsiblities. I figured it would be like most schools where I would have to TA freshmen my first or second year. I found out that I could be teaching first year medical students. This is both scary and really cool. I may be nervous to teach people that may be older than I am and not respect me but at the same time I can finally take revenge on all those grade hungry pre-med students. I should tell them the first day that if they look at me the wrong way or ask dumb questions in class they fail.
Daniell is sad and wants the semester to be over. In 12 hours she gets her break but  she may have already gone crazy

Because I'm a strange person I was going to go take the Organic Chemistry final for fun. I'm sure Schray wouldn't mind. However, I just discovered that my Bios367 exam is at the same time. Bummer. I would go take the Chem25 but I think I might fail it and that would depress me.

So they changed the name of Penn State Delco to Penn State Brandywine becasue they wanted to take the "Delaware" out of Penn State. People don't you realize that Brandywine is in New Castle County Delaware.  What about Penn State Media, Lima or just plain southeastern PA.
Youo know your life might be too busy when you find yourself schedualling in showers in your assignment book.

I looked at the final exam schedual. The good news is I only have 2 finals since upper level labs and humanites classes don't have final exams. The bad news is I have one exam on the first day and one on the last and nothing in between.

So this morning in the news a Kuztown University student was beaten to death by fellow students.  WTF. I used to be shocked when Lehigh students stole from each other freshman year. Now college students are murdering each other. What are they teaching you in high school?
Someone named a protein Sonic hedgehog (Shh). That kicks ass.

there is a GEICO ad in the Journal of Science. Yes there are a few ads in Science but they are for lab supplies or grant services.  I want to kill that lizard that is staring at me right now. No, I do not want you to help me save hundreds on my car insurance.

I'm so sad that my spectacular weekend is over.  Spending the weekend with Elaine and friends plus Harry Potter 3D IMAX was the shit.  (A whole lot of Harry was digitally in my lap) Don's GPS even had the voice of a British woman that instructed us how to get home. I'm just sad that we couldn't get a British man named Nigle on the GPS.

So our vice provost for Institutional Research was arrested in Delco for wanting to meet a mother and 2 children for sex.  They say most of the emails to arrange this meeting took place in the admissions building.  They quoted him saying he wanted to show the 11 year old "how to take a man." 

Way to go Lehigh, they sure can hire winners.

My job this summer involves playing with prostate cancer cells in hopes of killing the little bastards. But it occured to me today that I have no idea what a prostate does or how cancer forms.  I find the male reproductive system complicated with so much ducts and tubing. This is an interesting bit of knowledge I found.

Prostate cancer is one of the most common cancers affecting elderly men in developed countries and a major cause of death. Regular rectal exams are recommended for older men to detect prostate cancer early. Research has shown that regular ("more than five times per week"[2]) masturbation can cut the risk of prostate cancer by up to 66%. This is because regular ejaculation reduces the buildup of carcinogenic deposits in sperm which can damage the cells lining the prostate. This also applies to frequent sexual intercourse although the risks associated with STD's have been shown to increase risk of prostate cancer[3]. Once the lining of the prostate is affected with cancer, the only known treatments are surgery and radiation therapy. Both may limit the ability to have erection afterwards.

Taken from the University of Pennsylvania website...

The Department of Biology occupies four buildings, of which three - Leidy, Kaplan, and Mudd - are physically connected; the fourth, Goddard Laboratory, is directly adjacent to the Leidy Laboratory. The Leidy Laboratory, a Cope and Stewardson building, stands on Hamilton Walk and was built in 1910-11. Behind Leidy stands the Kaplan Wing, built in two phases: 1959-1960 and 1963-64. Behind the Kaplan wing is the Seely Mudd biological Research Laboratory, built 1984-86. The Bio Pond, located behind these facilities, provides a taste of nature on campus and a popular spot to relax or study on sunny days.

So as part of my virology course we were assigned to read an article from the New England Journal of Medicine on the HPV vaccine. I found the following statistics disturbing...

according to 2003 data 7.4% of adolescents initiate sexual activity before 13 years of age, about 1/3 of them by 9th grade, and about 2/3 by the end of high school.

I'm sorry but 13 year olds should not be having sex.

So since I have so many "interesting" opinions of Spiderman 3 I have desided to share them.  Don't worry I won't spoil anything but I will say what was not in the movie that should have been. I guess I will start out with that.

How the symbiotic creature got to earth was the lamest thing imaginable.  Those of you who watched the 90's cartoon series would agree with me here given what happed in a 25 minute cartoon kicked the shit out of what happened in the movie.  In the greatest moment in Saturday morning cartoon history it unfolded.  Astronauts took a space shuttle to the moon and discovered a strange "rock" and packed it back on the shuttle. One of the astronauts is Jamison's son who was actually a character in the first movie so I don't understand why the plot line didn't make it into the new movie.  Well on the way back to Earth the thing starts attacking and causes them to crash the shuttle into the George Washington Bridge like a makeshift runway.  Even in a cartoon crashing huge ass shuttles into big fucking bridges with cars and pavement flying everywhere is cool.  With special effects just imagine what that could of looked like in a movie.

Other than that my comments are that there were too many cheesy lines and Peter Parker had serious emo hair going on when he was in evil mode.

Overall I liked the movie but the second one was better. Though I do feel that Stan Lee is very anti-physics because all of his evil characters are physics experiments gone wrong.

If you know me you are aware that I am very enviromentally conscious.  I always try to recycle and conserve energy and so on.  Today I had to throw out a plastic bottle after my class in Williams.  Of course the plastic bin had a few other bottles in it as it should.  I had to throw out some paper in Iacocca and I actually walked all the way down the hall so I could throw it out in the paper bin and naturally the bin had paper in it. 

Now heres the punchline.  I was in Rauch for lunch and I had to throw my bottle out.  I discovered to dispite having a trash can every 2 feet in the area with the tables upstairs the plastic bin was filled with regular trash.   Groups on campus pushed hard last year to make sure there were more recycling bins around but what difference does it make if people are too stupid to use them.

Financial aid applications suck.

How the hell am I supposed to know how much my dad got payed in 2005 or the value of tax deferred annuity or the value of your parents home. 

If it doesn't say it on tax returns which I can look up I have no idea how they want me to get this information.  And also, I pay for my own school. How do my parents' finances have anything to do with paying for college.  Even if they made a million dollars my ablity to pay would be the same.

So I was looking through the AXE treasurer log book from 2005. At some point when Sarah was treasurer it says "Jeremy-Beverages -$265.45" I know this is probably for the semi formal since there are entries about it right before that but it still seems sketch.

Yay, I'm alive.
The past few days have not been fun with my 2nd major illness in the same school year.  I though I would be more likely to get sick living in doorms but I guess radiator heating provides no air circulation in houses like mine.  I have to say that in 2 years of campus housing I only got minor colds (the sinus infection freshman year came from the skeevy Virginia hotel room so that doesn't count)

In a matter of a few hours I went from feeling fine on Friday to puking my guts out, then to fever and muscle aches. Saturday I felt so horrible and dehydrated and I would have given anything for a drink without it hurting. I guess I looked as bad as I felt becasue Bruner, Matt, and Don collectivly desided to take me to the hospital. I really didn't want to go but I guess it was a good idea in the end.  Everything went pretty smooth in terms of getting to see a doctor without waiting for hours. An evil nurse stuck me with lots of needles and wasn't very comforting but overall the IV she gave me felt like happy running into my viens.  I had a nice room all to myself but it was pretty lonely until they let everyone in to see me.  If I design hospital rooms I will put flat pannel TVs on the ceiling. 

On Sunday I think I slept a record breaking amount of time and was only awake for about 4 hours.  
Monday was my first soild food- a banana. I was so proud of myself
I could really go for Wendys right now becasue I haven't eaten a proper meal since Friday at lunch but that is probably not a good idea. My goal then is Wendy's for Wednesday.

I can't seem to figure this all out because I should be dead by now, or at least puking my brains out.  

First Jim's flu like sickness.
After having the lung infection in November I was supposed to get a flu shot because my lungs were damaged and I could get flu so easily.  I never got one then Jim gets sick.  After spending considerable time around him while he was both dying and recovering I didn't get sick.

Pink Eye
The plague of the ME department.  It seemed that all the Mechanical Engineers were getting pink eye like Packard was harboring it or something. Christian got it and then my roommate Liz got it in both eyes. I feared that if I got infected it would be devistating with the open wounds in my eyes. I really don't want to go blind anytime soon. But so far, no pink eye.

Puking Sickness
Matt and I ate the same things on Friday night, share a bottle of Mountain Dew, take turns biting a candy bar, and sleep in the same room.  Matt wakes up throwing up with a 102 fever and I'm fine.  Do basically the same thing Saturday night when he was feeling a little better and still feel fine Sunday morning. Sunday night Jim starts throwing up and not me. (Jim was not even near Matt most of the weekend and he was better from the first sickness)

I bet everything is incubating inside of me and I will wake up near death tomorrow.

I have a feeling that this semester will not suck as much as last semester in terms of work load and frustration. Here was my experience so far.

Monday
8:10am Physics II- Its in RB so yay for living right across the street but boo for waking up early. Our professor seems ok and class is only 3 times a week instead of 4 like last semester.

2 hour break- I drove to UPS and had a hell of a time finding the entrance. The schedule gap is kind of annoying but I'll probably go to work in this time.

11:10 Virology Bios353- small class of 11 people and Dr. Sands loves me. Also, no required text book so yay for no money spent. However he did try to scare us with the "this is a 300 level blaa blaa and this is graduate level work blaa blaa" Grading is very different. No exams just projects and an open notes final worth 50% of our grade. Could be good could be bad.

Tuesday
9:20 EES100 Earth Systems science- seems interesting and there are field trips! Jessie and Sara are in there with me too so yay friends. Also, no final just a final project.

10:45 Bios 345 Molecular Genetics- Its in the distance room in Packer which is really over stimulating. There are 3 smart boards 2 flat panel TV and a big screen all projecting a combination of Dr. Wares face and the slides. I don't know where to look. Dr. Ware seemed really happy to see me and was even disappointed that Dr. Kuchka wouldn't let me take the lab. We should get along well.

1:10 Phys 22- silly lab, silly TA, and I miss my freshman that I used to abuse. I wonder how my TA would react to me calling her Physics lady since I can't say her name correctly.

Birthday weekend was awesome. Friday Saturday and Sunday of good times. And I finally got my fucking birthday song and free ice cream in Delaware without drowning in the margareta. Yay for Doug's birthday being on Friday for more free food. I could say more but I need to catch up on my beauty sleep.
So the wireless I was stealing wasn't working today so I found an alternative. If I plug my labtop into the phone line I can dial into lehigh's network.  Much coolness.
My parents are being bitches. They won't let me drive anywhere farther than down the street for fear that the Neon will blow up or something.

So today I had a lovely trip to King of Prussia to have a super-fun 2 hour "eye evaluation". If you don't know what I mean just think about why I don't wear contacts and then imagine similar activities for 2 hours. Most of the time I had an (I want to call her a nurse)annoying woman directing me through the different scanners. These things were like toucher devices and she got so pissed off when I couldn't keep my eye open for some of them. I was so relieved when I finally got the doctor who would be doing my surgery. He had enough sense to realize that my eyes were drying out so he gave me drops and helped me by pulling my eye open for me. I was scared about if I could handle the actual surgery but he made me feel better by testing a laser on my eye to see if I would flinch. surprisingly I didn't feel much. He even told me he would give me 2 tranquilizers instead of 1 if I was really uneasy.

I am sad that most of my friends don't post on LJ anymore. For some people this was the only way I felt in touch with them when I was at Lehigh. I don't even post that much anymore because I feel it is pointless to write long entries that I don't think anyone is reading. I some people don't write their own entries but they would at least leave comments letting me know that they were still around.

I guess I'm just sad in general because I'm really bored and I want to go back to Lehigh already. I've been here about 24 hours and am lonely and the lack of fast internet saddens me.

Inspiring quote I thought up this morning around 5:30am

Studying is like picking a basket of apples. Its easy in the beginning. There are so many apples and you easily start filling the basket. However, after awhile the basket gets really heavy and you get tired of carrying it. That is about the time that you should go home and rest and just be satisfied with what you have. If you get too tired you might trip and fall and loss all the apples you have in an attempt to get more.

I finally have a reason to feel good about something. I have finished all my math classes at Lehigh. My prof emailed me my grade and I got an A. 

To bad I still have 2 more finals to prepare for.

I went crazy this afternoon. What do I mean by crazy? I mean I couldn't sit still and felt the overpowering urge to scream at nothing in particular. My face was turning red and I wasn't doing anything except sitting in my chair.

I feel a little better now after my biochemistry final. It was an annoying test. I finished in an hour but then sat there staring at in for another 30 minutes. It had matching sections and normally I would think "great, yay for process of elimination." NO. It had double the number of choices then actual answers and you had to "pick the best answer". There were up to five right answers but one was "more right" then the others.

I had a dream last night that was so clear I feel it was a sign.
I was flying home from some unknown location but we first had to land in Pittsburgh and I had to change planes to go to Philly. As the plane lowered to land I saw in great detail all the buildings below. But there was something wrong on the runway and we couldn't land. The plane started doing crazy maneuvers and I thought we were going to crash. But all turned out well and we landed. Unfortunately for me I was late for my next flight because of the commotion and was running through the airport yelling for someone to help me find my terminal. I was carrying around a huge bag and someone showed me into what looked like a hotel room becasue they thought I was tired. I remember there was a huge spider on the bed and I ran out and continued to try to get my plane. I woke up not knowing if I ever got home.

Interpretation
My finals start tomorrow and I'm ready to crash and burn. But in the end I will come out of the first one safely despite my fear. However, I will soon become confused when the other finals start because the first one held me back. I will be dragging around this huge burden of 3 more tests. People will tell me to relax but relaxing may hurt me (big spider in bed).

I wish I found out what happened to me in the airport

I actually did work today! I studied biochemistry because I have not looked at any notes since the last test in October. I did get off to a late start though because sleeping till 11:30 seemed like a good idea. Around 3:30 I decided to make a record breaking 2nd trip to the health center in one year.  Since my ribs have only gotten worse in the 3 weeks of pain I felt I needed to get this checked out again considering I had trouble breathing last night. I actually got to see the real doctor this time.  I had a lovely time getting felt up and made to "forcibly exhale" 35 times. I get some fun anti-inflammatories that are illegal for athletes. But sadly he said that cartilage tares can take months to heal.

CaptainRonfornow: So you study yet or just killing more time?
Drowles04: I'm reading my biochemistry book. I'm not feeling it though. Its dull

Drowles04: that sounds like fun
Drowles04: maximum parsimony becomes maximum penis

So yesterday was cold and when it gets cold heaters become necessary. We turned our heat in the afternoon and it was making a really strange sound. We decided that this was not good and called the"fixing stuff guy" across the street. He said that our heater was not exshusing and we could either be warm and die of carbon monoxide poisoning or turn it off on the coldest night of the year. The house wasn't too bad until the sun went down and it dropped to 45 deg in my room. I couldn't feel my toes while sitting at my desk. Thankfully I was rescued by Burner in the EMS truck who took me to his  house. I think I confused Bryan when he saw me in the bathroom in my Pj's brushing my teeth. He pretty much pointed and said "you, why you are living in my house."

I think the pain in my ribs is getting worse. I need a nap. I don't feel like doing my work. The work that I hand in sucks.

Thank you LJ for giving me this opportunity to vent anger.
